**[Entry][1]** (and `Element` in general!) have an [`Id` property][2] that can be retrieved when you need it, to uniquely identify them.

If you have an `Entry myEntry`, then you can identify it on your event handler as:

    Entry myEntry = new Entry()
    {
        Id = Guid.NewGuid()
    };

    ...

    void Entry_Completed (object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        var entryID = ((Entry)sender).Id; //cast sender to access the properties of the Entry
        if (entryID.ToString() == myEntry.Id.ToString())
        {
            // Do something...
        }
    }

I hope that helps! 

