`useEffect` needs a dependency array as second argument, otherwise it keeps running on each render. Since you are updating state, this just keeps repeating

```
useEffect(() =&gt; {
  listener();
  return () =&gt; {
    listener();
  };
}, []);
```

[Docs](https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-effect.html)

You can use tools like [Runaway Effects](https://github.com/kentcdodds/stop-runaway-react-effects) or ESLint for static analysis for figuring these out beforehand.

